    "body": "### Problem\n\nUI when setting `statusline=foo`, as expected:\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/26609879/dd7a0f10-0bd3-4a68-b6c8-396f16bb3d36)\r\n\r\nUI when after that setting `laststatus=0`:\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/26609879/67c4c0fa-5edb-41c6-844a-54a19e80930d)\r\n\r\nDefault statusline appears in the cmdline (`0,0-1 All`)\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\r\n:set statusline=foo\r\n:set laststatus=0\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCmdline should not contain statusline, but if so, should respect `statusline` setting.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1011+g7bf0963d48\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux 6.4.9-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.12.2 (9d9982df)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nneovim-git AUR",
